content: Additionally, the Gen X (people born between 1965 and 1980) is also considered to be an active group of home buyers, as they are often at the peak of their earning potential and are looking to settle down in a permanent residence. It is also worth noting that the Baby Boomer generation (people born between 1946 and 1964) are also active in the housing market, as many are looking to downsize or move to retirement communities. Overall, the interest in buying a house can vary depending on individual circumstances, but generally, it is seen that people in the age group of late 20s to early 50s are the most interested in buying a house.
